.SS "15.15b rkyv KV Store (Phase 1 local)"
First-class CRUD store with rkyv as the on-disk codec. Zero-copy reads
(\fBmmap\fR + \fBvalidate\fR + \fBcast\fR), atomic rewrite on commit,
versioned format header. World-first: no other scripting language ships
a zero-copy archive KV as a core builtin.
.PP
.B kv_open kv_put kv_set kv_get kv_del kv_remove kv_exists kv_has
.B kv_keys kv_scan kv_len kv_count kv_size kv_commit kv_flush
.B kv_batch kv_close kv_stats kv_info
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
my $db = kv_open("/tmp/cache.rkyv");
kv_put($db, "users:alice", { name => "Alice", age => 30 });
kv_put($db, "users:bob",   { name => "Bob",   age => 28 });
kv_commit($db);

for my $row (kv_scan($db, "users:")) {
    my ($key, $val) = @$row;
    say "$key -> $val->{name}";
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
Phase 2 ships
.B stryke kvd
server + remote
.B kv_connect
client \(em the same rkyv archive bytes travel over TCP.
